cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a neural network-based attention model for chemical-disease relation extraction, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper utilizes prior knowledge from knowledge bases, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The attention mechanism used in the model also suggests relevance to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of neural networks implies a connection to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
